    "description": "Rikei Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the system and network solutions, and electronic components and instrument businesses in Japan and internationally. It provides system solutions, including IT infrastructure, information security, and 3D CAD, CAM, and CAE solutions; IBM; Hewlett Packard enterprise solutions; entrance exam/curriculum and secure file collaboration systems; non-contact vital measurement and cloud SaaS solutions; IoT products; PCs; cloud authentication solution; software for power systems EMT simulations and calculating cable current carrying capacity; and AI products to private companies, universities, government offices, and research institutions. The company also offers information transmission and distribution network solutions to broadcasters, telecommunications, and local governments; and electronic components, instruments, and electronic materials for various sectors, including industrial equipment, automobile, medical, optical communication, and security. In addition, it engages in the sale and lease of aircraft and aircraft parts, and customer support; system development activities; and export, import, and sale of electronic products. The company was formerly known as Rikei Trading Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Rikei Corporation in June 1971. Rikei Corporation was incorporated in 1957 and is headquartered in Shinjuku, Japan."
